<plot>New York City - Present Day When the "old lady" across the hall dies, Abigail Clayton gets new neighbors. And they want more than a cup of sugar. Witness an elaborate scheme to steal the identity of a wealthy, agoraphobic heiress. A scheme that has the only person she cares about as its mastermind. After Lillian moves in, Abigail begins to hear strange activity and conversations from across the way. After a horribly abusive night with Charlie, Lillian is left half dead. Reluctantly, Abigail comes to her aid. This is the first new relationship Abigail has had since she was a child. The two women quickly find they have much in common and a unique friendship begins to develop. But what starts out benign, slowly turns dangerous as we come to realize Lillian's true intentions - to infiltrate Abigail's life and steal her identity, her fortune and everything that matters to her. How can a woman, who nobody knows exists, and can't leave her house, protect herself when all around her are closing in?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?111273</url></doc>
